<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Harlem Renaissance of the 1920s was characterized by:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">African American cultural and artistic flourishing</option>
            <option letter="b">Political reforms in New York City</option>
            <option letter="c">Immigration restrictions</option>
            <option letter="d">Economic development programs</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Harlem Renaissance was a period of extraordinary African American cultural expression, particularly in literature and arts. Writers like Langston Hughes and Countee Cullen, along with musicians and artists, created works celebrating Black identity and experience, making Harlem the cultural capital of Black America during the 1920s.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
